This film took a simple route and just concentrated on one particular night where 3 characters meet and interact. Definitely worth a watch.
In total, Irul just feels like a chapter from a novel is filmed as there were no backstories for the characters. In my opinion,a backstory for a character is no longer necessary.

Dharsana who played Archana was good. Although the runtime of the film was only 1 hour 30 mins, the film seems to be kinda draggy. The usual twists and turns should have been avoided, though it was filmed in a convincing way.

Fahadh again outstands everyone with his top notch performance.He perfectly fitted the role,Unni unlike Soubin who played Alex.Though the actor somehow hardly managed to keep the mysterious feel flowing, a better casting for this role would have helped the film more convincingly.

The denial of the characters were portrayed with Rashomon effect which is very impressive. These scenes were beautifully written. Situations were used smartly by the characters to frame each other. This keeps the audience engaged throughout the film.

The film revolves around 3 characters played by #FahadhFaasil , Soubin Shabir and Darshana Rajendran. The interesting point of the film is that the conversation among themselves soon suggests that there's a serial killer among them.

@dopjomon's cinematography is striking with amazing lighting and camera angles. It really enhanced the dark element of the film. @SreeragSaji 's chilling music with excellent cinematography took the entire film to an international standard.

#Irul - 3.75/5
